[The above newswire mentions 2 additional cases that do not appear to be included in the official data reported as of 5 Jan 2012 (see [1]Worldwide - 2011 data as of 5 Jan 2011) as the date of onset of most recent case in the official report is listed as 16 Jan 2012, whereas the case in Khyber Agency had a date of onset of 23 Dec 2012, and the case in FATA had a date of onset of 18 Dec 2012. These 2 cases highlight the challenges confronting the goal of interruption of WPV transmission in Pakistan. In one case, the child was not adequately vaccinated because of civil strife leading to interruptions in service delivery. In the other case, the child was not vaccinated because of religious objection to vaccination -- most likely due to the rumors circulating in Pakistan that the vaccine is a western plot to induce sterility in vaccine recipients, as the predominant religion in the FATA region Islam, is not a religion that bans the use of childhood vaccines.

For a map of Pakistan showing administrative divisions, see http://www.mapsofworld.com/pakistan/pakistan-political-map.html. The Kyber-Pakhtunkhwa area borders with the FATA (Federally Administered Tribal Areas), which borders with Afghanistan, where there is also continued transmission of WPV (see official data below). - Mod.MPP]

