[3] Nigeria - 22 states WPV free 3 years
Date: 7 Jan 2012
Source: All Africa
http://allafrica.com/stories/201201061165.html


Nigeria: 22 States in Nigeria Are Polio Free - NPHCDA
----------------
The Executive Director of the National Primary Health Care Development Agency, NPHCDA, Dr Ado Mohammed, has disclosed that 22 States in Nigeria have remained polio free for 3 years even as the country is among the 4 most endemic polio countries in the world.

Ado, who spoke in an interview in Minna, yesterday, said that as at the end of January 2011, the country has recorded as low as 51 cases of wild polio virus [WPV] in only 8 States.

According to him, the statistics represent 90 per cent of reduction in wild polio virus spread in the country as the country set 80 percent vaccine coverage in order to prevent further spread of the virus.

The Executive Director, who was in Minna for a one day sensitisation meeting of stakeholders on polio eradication and routine immunisation, disclosed that a national task team has been constituted to stop transmission of the diseases in the country by the end of this year [2012].

He said, "An immediate outcome of the task team's work is the accountability frame work to hold the federal, states, local government and our partners accountable for polio eradication".

[Byline: Abu Nmodu]

