Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[[For a map of Nigeria showing states, see http://allafrica.com/stories/201201061165.html. There are presently 36 states and a Federal Capital Territory (Abuja). Hence, the above report that 22 states are now WPV free for 3 or more years means that 59 percent of the states and Federal Capital Territory have been WPV long enough to be considered as having eradicated WPV in these states. Unfortunately, there are still 8 states with active transmission of WPV, some of which include states that had the vaccination activities seriously interrupted back in 2003/2004 due to rumors similar to those affecting Pakistan today (see above report [2] Pakistan - New 2011 cases since official report in [1]). One hopes that the current transmission is not related to persist pockets of population that refuse vaccination based on the old rumors.

For the interactive HealthMap/ProMED map of Nigeria, see http://healthmap.org/r/1qGF - Mod.MPP]]
